Nigeria’s Senate President, Ahmed Lawan, has said that President Muhammadu Buhari will on Thursday present the 2021 Appropriation Bill to a joint session of the National Assembly. Buhari’s letter of request was read on Tuesday during plenary by Lawan.  “May I crave the kind indulgence of the Distinguished Senate to grant me the slot of 11:00hrs on Thursday, 8th October, 2020, to formally present the 2021 Appropriation Bill to the joint session of the National Assembly. “While I look forward to addressing the joint session, please, accept Mr Senate President, the assurances of my highest regard,” part of the letter read.